<p>Significant radiation doses are not frequently encountered in everyday l=
ife. The following examples can help illustrate relative magnitudes; these =
are meant to be examples only, not a comprehensive list of possible radiati=
on doses. An "acute dose" is one that occurs over a short and finite period=
 of time, while a "chronic dose" is a dose that continues for an extended p=
eriod of time so that it is better described by a dose rate.
</p>
