<p>Although the United States Nuclear Regulatory Commission permits the use=
 of the units <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Curie_(unit)" title=
=3D"Curie (unit)">curie</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rad_(=
radiation_unit)" title=3D"Rad (radiation unit)">rad</a>, and <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roentgen_equivalent_man" title=3D"Roentgen equiv=
alent man">rem</a> alongside SI units,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-88" class=3D"refe=
rence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sievert#cite_note-88"><span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>84<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a>=
</sup> the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_Union" title=
=3D"European Union">European Union</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/European_units_of_measurement_directives" title=3D"European units of m=
easurement directives">European units of measurement directives</a> require=
d that their use for "public health ... purposes" be phased out by 31 Decem=
ber 1985.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-89" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Sievert#cite_note-89"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</sp=
an>85<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Rem_equivalence">Rem equiva=
lence</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-brac=
ket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DSiever=
t&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D29" title=3D"Edit section: Rem equivalenc=
e"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></div>
<p>An older unit for the dose equivalent is the <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Roentgen_equivalent_man" title=3D"Roentgen equivalent man">re=
m</a>,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-EPA_90-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sievert#cite_note-EPA-90"><span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">[</span>86<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> still often use=
d in the United States. One sievert is equal to 100 rem:
</p>
